e molecules\ncontaining the S2 unit are up to two orders of magnitude lower than the H2S\nabundance in the source, and one order of magnitude lower than the expected\nabundances from the experimental simulations using ice analogs. Subsequent\ngas-phase chemistry after desorption could lower the abundances of the three\nspecies to undetectable levels in our observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Jan 2016 16:15:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-12"}
