lls with different adhesion matrices compete for reproduction,\nshowing that, in our model, structural organization can improve the fitness of\na given cell population. The implications of these results for ecological and\nevolutionary models of pattern formation and the emergence of multicellularity\nare outlined.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Jan 2016 15:35:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-23"}
